Dusk on Cluny Townhouse, Paris HDR
<b>[fr]</b>: Tombée de la nuit sur le Musée Cluny, <a href="http://www.flickr.com/search/?q=paris&amp;m=tags&amp;w=41324014@N00&amp;s=int">Paris</a>, France

<b>[image info]</b>: HDR from 5 different exposures - Photomatix - Nikon D200 - tripod - Sigma  10-20mm@10mm - 8000K WB - EXIF from +1ev

<b>[Level of Retouching]</b>: 40% (HDR processing, perspective correction, local levels and curves adjustments, local photo filters) - total processing: 40 minutes

<b>[Original picture]</b>: I will not do that on each HDR I upload here, but in this case see below the untouched 0ev image.

<b>[comment]</b>: it seems that HDR does not leave people indifferent and It's funny to see how it has grown  controversial subject among photographers like the Canon vs Nikon and Mac Vs PC debates. 

It is OKAY if you don't like HDR (even if some rant about HDR pictures which are not...lol... in fact, what they don't like is usually the tonemapping/detail enhancement/micro contrast adjustments), but respect the work of others. 

